---
// Ported from _src/pages/lesson-logger.html via scripts/port-page.mjs.
// SEO mirrors tests/seo-fixture.json.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Lesson Logger: Capture Lessons Before They Vanish | Jevan Goldsmith"
  description="A simple lesson-logging page for turning mistakes, wins, and observations into reusable judgment."
  canonical="https://jevangoldsmith.com/lesson-logger.html"
>
<main class="experience-content">
        <header class="experience-header">
            <p class="experience-eyebrow">Learning in Public</p>
            <h1 class="experience-title">Lesson Logger</h1>
            <p class="experience-subtitle">Insights and lessons I've picked up along the way. Writing them down helps me remember and hopefully helps others too.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="lessons-timeline">
            <div class="year-divider">
                <span class="year-divider-text">2026</span>
                <div class="year-divider-line"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="lesson-item">
                <div class="lesson-marker">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="lesson-date">February 2026</span>
                <div class="lesson-card">
                    <span class="lesson-category mindset">Mindset</span>
                    <h3 class="lesson-title">The best time to start was yesterday. The second best time is now.</h3>
                    <p class="lesson-content">Spent too long researching the "perfect" way to build this website before realizing I just needed to start. Perfectionism is procrastination in disguise. Ship it, then iterate.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lesson-item">
                <div class="lesson-marker">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="lesson-date">January 2026</span>
                <div class="lesson-card">
                    <span class="lesson-category finance">Finance</span>
                    <h3 class="lesson-title">Your lifestyle should lag your income by at least two years</h3>
                    <p class="lesson-content">After completing a no-spend month, realized how much lifestyle inflation had crept in. The gap between what you earn and what you spend is what creates freedom.</p>
                    <div class="lesson-source">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"/><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2z"/></svg>
                        <span>Learned from: <a href="/books.html">The Psychology of Money</a></span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lesson-item">
                <div class="lesson-marker">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="lesson-date">January 2026</span>
                <div class="lesson-card">
                    <span class="lesson-category business">Business</span>
                    <h3 class="lesson-title">Focus on inputs, not outputs</h3>
                    <p class="lesson-content">Can't control whether a project succeeds, but can control showing up every day and doing the work. Focusing on process over outcomes reduces anxiety and increases consistency.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="year-divider">
                <span class="year-divider-text">2025</span>
                <div class="year-divider-line"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="lesson-item">
                <div class="lesson-marker">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="lesson-date">December 2025</span>
                <div class="lesson-card">
                    <span class="lesson-category relationships">Relationships</span>
                    <h3 class="lesson-title">Be the friend who reaches out first</h3>
                    <p class="lesson-content">Everyone is waiting for someone else to make the first move. The person who initiates builds the deepest relationships. Don't keep score on who texted last.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lesson-item">
                <div class="lesson-marker">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="lesson-date">November 2025</span>
                <div class="lesson-card">
                    <span class="lesson-category life">Life</span>
                    <h3 class="lesson-title">Travel while you're young and healthy</h3>
                    <p class="lesson-content">You can always make more money, but you can't make more time or recapture youth. The experiences and perspectives gained from travel are irreplaceable.</p>
                    <div class="lesson-source">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0 1 18 0z"/><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"/></svg>
                        <span>Learned from: <a href="/adventures.html">Japan trip</a></span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lesson-item">
                <div class="lesson-marker">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="lesson-date">October 2025</span>
                <div class="lesson-card">
                    <span class="lesson-category mindset">Mindset</span>
                    <h3 class="lesson-title">You don't rise to the level of your goals, you fall to the level of your systems</h3>
                    <p class="lesson-content">Goals are for setting direction. Systems are for making progress. After failing to stick to vague resolutions, started building specific daily habits instead.</p>
                    <div class="lesson-source">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"/><path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2z"/></svg>
                        <span>Learned from: <a href="/books.html">Atomic Habits</a></span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
</main>
</Base>
